div.p:
Ambassador Goldberg: I am still opposed. I do not think it will bring them to the
                    conference table. I am the least expert of any in this room, but I can see these
                    risks: 

—More involvement of North Vietnam in the South;

—No real shortage of supplies (Red China has plenty for them);

—More involvement by the Chinese;

—More involvement by the Soviets; (It is inconceivable that they can
                            allow this significant action to pass without reaction of some
                            kind.)

—Attrition of friends abroad and people at home.
